tspan.tspan: Fly Escape is a boot sector game developed by Krzysztof Krystian
Jankowski ^ P1X, released version 2.1 on May 26, 2024.
The game runs on Intel 286 processors in 16-bit real mode and
features a simple yet engaging gameplay experience in a VGA
The objective of the game is to control a fly, avoid spiders,
and collect flowers to advance through levels.
